@startuml network-scenario-hotspot
!include _standard-style.puml
title **Scenario D — Mobile Hotspot (4G/5G Tethering)**
caption INSIDE_CN=false | No VPN | Direct internet via carrier | Cellular-specific quirks

left to right direction

' === WORKSTATION ===
rectangle "**Workstation** (localhost)" as WS #F0FFF0 {

  rectangle "Local Proxy (per OS)" as PROXY #FFF8E1 {
    component "**macOS**: Proxydetox :3128\nDIRECT fallback (PAC unreachable)" as mac_proxy <<core>>
    component "**Windows**: px :3128\nDIRECT fallback" as win_proxy <<core>>
    component "**WSL**: CNTLM :3128 or unset\nhttps_proxy" as wsl_proxy <<core>>
    component "**Linux**: CNTLM :3128 or unset\nhttps_proxy" as lnx_proxy <<core>>
  }

  rectangle "Applications" as APPS #FFFFFF {
    component "Browser" as browser <<cli>>
    component "VS Code + Copilot" as vscode <<cli>>
    component "Git (HTTPS)" as git_https <<cli>>
    component "Git (SSH)" as git_ssh <<cli>>
    component "curl / npm / Docker" as cli_tools <<cli>>
  }
}

' === CELLULAR NETWORK ===
rectangle "**Cellular Network (Carrier)**" as CELL #FFECB3 {
  component "**Carrier NAT / CGN**\n(Carrier-Grade NAT)\nShared public IP" as cgn <<infra>>
  component "**Carrier DNS**\nNo *.bmwgroup.net resolution\nPotentially slow (>3s)" as cdns <<infra>>

  note bottom of CELL
    **Cellular-specific issues:**
    • DNS resolution can be slow (>3s) — may trigger
      detect-network.sh timeout → false negative
    • Carrier-Grade NAT (CGN) — shared IP, some services
      may rate-limit or flag shared IPs
    • MTU issues possible (cellular MTU < 1500)
    • Connection may drop briefly during handover (cell tower switch)
    • IPv6-only carriers: some tools may fail without IPv4
    • **No corporate DNS** → INSIDE_CN=false
  end note
}

' === ENDPOINTS ===
rectangle "**External Endpoints**" as EXT #E8F4FD {
  component "**cc-github.bmwgroup.net**\nGHE :443 / :22" as ghe <<api>>
  component "**api.github.com**\nCopilot :443" as gh_api <<api>>
  component "**api.anthropic.com**\nClaude :443" as anthropic <<api>>
  component "**npm / Docker**\nregistries :443" as registries <<api>>
}

' === FLOW ===
browser --> mac_proxy
vscode --> mac_proxy
cli_tools --> mac_proxy
git_https --> mac_proxy
git_ssh -[#43A047,bold]-> cgn : SSH :22 (direct)

mac_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> cgn : DIRECT
win_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> cgn : DIRECT
wsl_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> cgn : DIRECT
lnx_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> cgn : DIRECT

cgn -[#43A047,bold]-> gh_api : ✓ Allowed
cgn -[#43A047,bold]-> anthropic : ✓ **Allowed** (no firewall)
cgn -[#43A047,bold]-> registries : ✓ Allowed
cgn -[#43A047,bold]-> ghe : ✓ SSH :22 (if DNS resolves)
cgn -[#E53935,dashed]-> ghe : ✗ DNS fails for\ncc-github.bmwgroup.net\n(internal only)

' === HEALTH MONITORING ===
rectangle "**Health Monitoring** (coding/bin/coding)" as HEALTH #E1BEE7 {
  note as hn
    **Detection**: DNS for muc.proxy-pac.bmwgroup.net FAILS
    → INSIDE_CN=false → network=open
    **Known issue**: Carrier DNS can be slow (>3s)
    → detect-network.sh may false-negative on direct connectivity test
    **Fix**: Script preserves proxy env vars, retests via proxy as fallback
    **Cellular handover**: Brief connection drops during cell tower switch
    → health-coordinator detects via failed probe, waits for recovery
    **Status line**: N:OPEN P:OFF LLM:●
    **Auto-heal**: Accelerated probing (5s interval) after connectivity loss
  end note
}

' === OS-SPECIFIC NOTES ===
note as os_notes
  **OS-Specific — Mobile Hotspot:**

  **macOS**: WiFi interface connects to phone hotspot.
  Proxydetox DIRECT fallback works transparently.
  May need to disable "auto-join" for corporate WiFi to prevent flip-flopping.

  **Windows**: Mobile hotspot via WiFi or USB tethering.
  px falls back to DIRECT. WinHTTP system proxy should be cleared.
  **WSL2 caveat**: Hyper-V vEthernet may not route through hotspot correctly
  — may need `wsl --shutdown` and reconnect.

  **Linux**: USB tethering (most reliable) or WiFi hotspot.
  NetworkManager handles interface switch.
  Unset https_proxy or let CNTLM fall back to DIRECT.

  **All**: Bandwidth-limited — large npm installs / Docker pulls may be slow.
  Consider using `--prefer-offline` for npm, cached Docker images.
end note

legend bottom
  |= Protocol |= Port |= Auth |= Status (Hotspot) |= Caveat |
  | HTTPS (Copilot) | 443 | OAuth Bearer | ✓ Works | Carrier DNS may be slow |
  | HTTPS (Claude) | 443 | API Key | ✓ **Works** | Bandwidth-dependent |
  | HTTPS (Git) | 443 | GCM / OAuth | ✓ Works | github.com only |
  | SSH (Git) | 22 | SSH Key | ✓ Works | github.com only |
  | HTTPS (GHE) | 443 | SSO | ✗ DNS fails | Internal DNS required |
end legend

@enduml
